  "course_description": "A course on topics of special biological interest, designed for Biology majors elective credit. This course is repeatable when the topic varies.",
  "course_notes": "(Same as NBB 370 2) This course covers how genes function in the nervous system to impact development, behavior, and disease. We will discuss studies across different organisms, from invertebrates to humans, and we will focus on reading and discussing primary literature. Prerequisites: Biology 142 + 142L or equivalent transfer credit. Prior coursework in neurobiology and/or genetics will be helpful, but is not required.",
